  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Key elements typically include:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of money through multiple transactions\n3. Integration: Making the funds appear legitimate\n\nSpecific legal definitions can vary by jurisdiction, but typically involve:\n- Deliberately concealing the origin of criminal proceeds\n- Transferring money to hide illegal sources\n- Attempting to make illegally obtained money seem legally earned\n\nSpecific laws like the Bank Secrecy Act and anti-money laundering regulations outline detailed legal standards.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering definitions?",
